  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The WE-CT is an innovative and easy practice imaging technique of colon tumors; it is based
      on the colon distension by a high volume of warm water and a multidetector CT acquisition
      after IV (intravenous) contrast, allowing image analysis including the wall thickness and
      enhancement, the pericolic adjacent spaces and the entire abdomen.

      The goal of the study is the evaluation of its performances for the diagnosis of colon
      tumors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
